LONDONJoe Root scored an unbeaten century as tournament hosts England beat Bangladesh by eight wickets in the opening match of the 2017 Champions Trophy at the Oval on Thursday.England, set 306 for victory, finished on 308 for two with 16 balls to spare.Root was a career-best 133 not out and England captain Eoin Morgan 75 not out, with their unbroken stand worth 143.Opener Alex Hales was out for 95.Earlier, Bangladesh made 305 for six after losing the toss.Tamim Iqbal top-scored with 128 and put on 166 for the third wicket with Mushfiqur Rahim (79).But when both batsmen were out in successive deliveries from fast bowler Liam Plunkett, the innings faltered.Plunkett led England's attack with four wickets for 59 runs from his maximum 10 overs.Brief scores:Bangladesh 305-6, 50 overs (Tamim Iqbal 128, Mushfiqur Rahim 79; L Plunkett 4-59)England 308-2, 47.2 overs (J Root 133 no, A Hales 95, E Morgan 75 no)Result: England won by eight wickets email print email print Kumble is an automatic candidate for a new contract.